rComments: He was an amazing prof, always stayed after class to help with assignments and answer any questions!
- explains content well - always available to ask for help with questions, even assignments - lectures feel long - good guy, good prof
Great professor. Clear in what he's teaching. Lectures move smoothly and don't feel like a math class that never ends.  A wonderful choice for any first year student transitioning to university math.
Dr Jeffrey Musgrave is a really awesome prof who helped me to check my assignment step by step and stay put at math department until I finished my assignment.

Really awesome prof! Speaks very clearly and communicates himself well. Always willing to help you out on assignments and such, but those are pretty easy anyway. Midterms and final were very straightforward with no surprises at all. Posts technique summaries and practice problems online, so take advantage of those and you will have an easy time.

Super helpful guy, gives you everything you need to succeed. He clearly cares about his students, and he always answers questions, even gives hints for tougher assignment problems in class. A truly excellent math prof, I wish more were like him.
Great guy that goes out of his way to help you do well.
Best math prof I ever had. Incredibly helpful, very clear explanations and very fair tests. Would highly recommend.
